## Roadmap

- [x] Proof of concept — single agent pair, browser demo
- [ ] Multi-agent network — multiple Beta agents, parallel screening
- [ ] Trust/verification layer — prevent spam agents
- [ ] Persistent agent profiles — agents remember past interactions
- [ ] MCP integration — plug into Anthropic’s Model Context Protocol
- [ ] A2A protocol support — Google’s Agent-to-Agent standard
- [ ] REST API — deploy your own agent node
- [ ] Agent registry — discover and connect with other agents

-----

## Tech Stack

- **AI Engine**: Claude API (Anthropic) / OpenAI API
- **Agent Framework**: Python (core), vanilla JS (demo)
- **Protocol**: Custom JSON schema over HTTPS (v0.1)
- **Future**: MCP / Google A2A for standardized agent communication

-----

## The Bigger Vision

This is v0.1 of what could become a global business intelligence layer. Every company deploys an agent node. Opportunity profiles flow through the network. Matches surface automatically. The right deals reach the right people.

The infrastructure is being built right now by Anthropic (MCP) and Google (A2A). NEXUS is the business logic layer on top.

